AGI - The family of the deceased Israeli prisoner Shiri Bibas, the mother of the little Kfir and Ariel, confirmed that his remains were identified by the Institute of Legal Medicine of Israel. Al Jazeera reports it.&nbsp; In a statement published on the Instagram account of Bring Bibas Back, the Bibas family said that experts from the Institute of Legal Medicine &nbsp; Abu Kabir in Tel Aviv. They identified Shiri Bibas' body. "This morning we received the news we feared most. Our Shiri was killed in captivity and now she is home to her children," said the family in a statement. No further details were given on the forensic examination.
<div </div
&nbsp;
Israeli kibbutz Nir Oz also confirmed this morning the death of the hostage of Argentine and Peruvian origin Shiri Bibas, whose body had not been returned to Israel on Thursday with those of his two sons, also kidnapped by Hamas. Yesterday the Red Cross announced that it had delivered new remains to Israel, but had not provided information on identity. A few hours later, the kibbutz in which the family lived said that Bibas "died in prison in Gaza" and now "will rest in the land of Israel with his two young children". &nbsp;>
<div </div
&nbsp;
The body delivered Friday by Hamas belongs to Shiri Bibas. The remains of the woman should have been delivered on Wednesday with those of the two sons, Ariel and Kfir Bibas, four years and nine months, and 83-year-old Oded Lifsthiz, but forensic tests had concluded that the remains delivered did not correspond to Shiri Bibas, while the other bodies were identified.
Hamas claimed that Shiri, Ariel and Kfir were killed in a bombing by Israeli planes in Gaza on days before the truce then in progress. But Israel has denied this reconstruction: "The Bibas brothers were killed by Hamas with bare hands." The confirmation of Shiri Bibas' identity coincides with the expectation of six hostages held by Hamas in exchange for the liberation of 602 Palestinian prisoners by Israel.&nbsp;
"Shiri was a wonderful mother for Ariel and Kfir, a loving companion for Yarden, a devoted sister and aunt and an incredible friend. Thank you all for your support and love over the past 16 months, we would like Shiri to be here to see it." It is the message sent by the Bibas family after the identification of Shiri Bibas' body, delivered yesterday by Hamas after the exchange of the remains the previous day. "We demanded certainty" about the fate of Shiri and the two sons Ariel and Kfir "for 16 months, and now there is no comfort in this">, he added.&nbsp;
<h2> <br> Hamas, from Israel absolute lies on the death of children
On the death of the two little Bibas, Israel only released "absolute bogies". Hamas reported it, pointing out that the accusation of the Jewish State against the Palestinian group of having killed them in bare hands "is a desperate attempt to evade the responsibility of its criminal army for the killing of the family". The Bibas died because of "the genocide, the brutal bombings, the widespread destruction of buildings and neighborhoods and the obstruction of the ceasefire agreement by the war criminal Netanyahu". &nbsp;
&nbsp;

