AGI - Israel accused the Palestinian movement Hamas of killing the children Ariel and Kfir Bibas > during their captivity in Gaza and having delivered the body of an unknown person instead of that of the mother Shiri, > of Argentine origin.
Subsequently, a source told Al Jazeera that Hamas delivered Shiri Bibas' body to the Red Cross > but the Israeli authorities have not yet confirmed the news. IDFs say they're reviewing the details. According to Al Arabya's correspondent, the body has not yet been delivered but Hamas will shortly deliver it to the Red Cross.&nbsp;
As provided for in the treasury agreement in Gaza, Hamas delivered four bodies that said belonging to the three members of the Bibas family and retired Israeli journalist Oded Lifshitz.
Shiri and his sons Ariel and Kfir, who were four years and eight months old when they were kidnapped on October 7, 2023, had become a symbol of the hostages taken by Hamas>. The father, also kidnapped, was released on February 1st.
&nbsp;
<div </div
<br The Palestinian Islamist movement claimed that the woman and the two children were killed during an Israeli bombing on Gaza in November 2023, but Israel had not confirmed it and their relatives hoped they were still alive. An Israeli military spokesman, Avichay Adraee, said that the analysis of the delivered bodies and available information indicated that "Ariel and Kfir Bibas were brutally murdered in captivity in November 2023 by Palestinian terrorists."
In his statement, the spokesman also denounced that "the extra body is not that of their mother, Shiri, nor that of any other Israeli hostage." It is a "unidentified" body, said Adraee, accusing Hamas of "a flagrant violation" of the truce agreement in Gaza and asking to "reestablish Shiri Bibas, as well as all persons abducted". &nbsp;
<h2>Hamas, the body of Shiri Bibas mistaken by mistake</h2>
There might be an involuntary exchange of bodies behind Shiri Bibas's failure to return. He was responsible for Hamas, Ismail al-Thawabteh, reporting the Times of Israel. Shiri's body was "appearingly mixed with other bodies under the rubble," he said reasserting that the Bibas died in an Israeli attack. &nbsp;
<h2>Hamas to Israel, give us back the body of the woman traded for Bibas</h2>
Hamas asked Israel to return the body of the Palestinian woman of Gaza who was delivered yesterday instead of the Israeli hostage Shiri Bibas. The Palestinian group has reiterated that it must be a "error" when the bodies were extracted from the rubble.
<h2>Hamas confirms the names of six live hostages to be released tomorrow</h2>
Hamas has confirmed that tomorrow he will release six hostages: Tal Shoham, Omer Shem-Tov, Eliya Cohen, Omer Wenkert, Avera Mengistu and Hisham al-Sayed. These are the last live abducts that will be released in the first phase of the agreement for the ceasefire in Gaza. Mengistu and Al-Sayed have been held in the Strip for a decade after entering into two different circumstances by mistake, the other four were taken hostage on 7 October 2023.
&nbsp;

